race.comment: WOOTTON VERNI (6) given the gun run by Damian Lane when relishing the 2000m to snare the G3 Coongy Cup at Caulfield. Peaking at the right time and Waller looks to have found a winnable race from the good gate. The one to beat. MAISON LOUIS (4) 2025 Queensland Derby winner who looks to have returned a decent four-year-old. Huge effort behind Lindermann when a slashing third in the G2 Hill Stakes over 1900m at Rosehill. Fitter now and expect Gibbons to make good use of the low draw. PALMETTO (5) Canberra Cup winner who can take control early fifth-up. No Lindermann to deal with today and will take running down. REDSTONE WELL (8) capable on his day and will appreciate the big weight drop out to the 2000m. Sherry sticks and will roll forward.
